'''Lax Ksiluux''' is the name of a former [[First Nations]] community in northwestern [[British Columbia]], Canada. It existed on the south side of the [[Nass River]] near a creek known as [[Ts'oohl Ts'ap]].<ref>[http://www.citytel.net/~nisga1/Gitwinksihlkw.html Gitwinksihlkw]{{dead link|date=July 2018}}</ref>

Lax Ksiluux was in existence prior to the eruption of [[Tseax Cone]] in the 18th century which buried the community with thick [[lava]] flows along with the nearby community of [[Wii Lax K'abit, British Columbia|Wii Lax K'abit]].<ref>{{BCGNIS|39898|Gitwinksihlkw}}</ref>

