{{italic title}}

'''''The Bomb''''' is a play by Kevin Dyer, focusing on the [[Irish Republican Army|IRA]] [[Brighton bomb]]ing of 1984.

==Plot==
In 2000, [[Jo Berry]], whose father was killed in the blast, met [[Patrick Magee (Irish republican)|Patrick Magee]], the man who planted the bomb. ''The Bomb'' is inspired by the events which led Jo and Patrick to meet and the impact those people had on each other.

It is sourced from interviews, research and actual and imagined dialogue. It is not a [[Verbatim theatre|verbatim play]], but is partly factual and describes real events.

''The Bomb'' has twice toured nationally.{{citation needed|date=May 2013}} ''The Bomb'' was nominated for two [[Theatrical Management Association Award|Theatrical Management Awards]].

